==English==
===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/'di:mən/}}

===Etymology 1===
[[Category:Greek derivations]]
From [[Ancient Greek]] '''[[δαίμων]]''' (''daemon'') " a god, goddess, divine power, genius, guardian spirit", from '''[[δαίω]]''' (''daio'') "to divide, to distribute destinies, to allot".

====Noun====
{{en-noun|daemon|daemons}}
#(''archaic'') a [[demon]].
#(''Greek mythology'') A lesser [[deity]] between [[men]] and [[god]]s.
# one's inner spirit or [[daimon]]

===Etymology 2===
Perhaps an abbreviation of [[disk]] [[and]] [[execution]] [[monitor]], or of [[device]] [[monitor]], or perhaps just an adaptation of Etymology 1.

====Noun====
{{en-noun|daemon|daemons}}
# {{cattag|Computing}} (''Unix''): A [[process]] (a running program) that does not have a controlling [[terminal]].

=====Usage notes=====
* (''Unix'') Often a '''daemon''' will be a [[server]].

=====See also=====
* [[background process]]

